In a televised address to Russians, President Putin claimed the operation is aimed at the "demilitarisation and denazification" of Ukraine. Major explosions were heard near major cities such as the capital Kiev at around 5 am on Thursday, with many Ukrainians fleeing their homes in fear. Ukrainian foreign minister Dmytro Kuleba said: "Putin has just launched a full-scale invasion of Ukraine. “Peaceful Ukrainian cities are under strikes. This is a war of aggression. Ukraine will defend itself and will win. The world can and must stop Putin. The time to act is now.”World leaders such as President Biden and President Macron have condemned the attacks. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES... 